In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Finely dice @tomato{1}(finely diced). Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1}(halved and cut into 1/2-inch-thick wedges); mince one wedge until you have 1 TBSP. Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered). Core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1}(deseeded and diced into 1/2-inch pieces). Mince @cilantro{1/4%oz}(minced).

In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, minced onion, and juice from half the lime; season with @salt{}.

Add @smoky red pepper crema{2%tbsp} to a separate small bowl. Stir in @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and onion wedges. Season with @salt{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly charred, ~{7-9%minutes}.

Transfer veggies to a plate.

Add another drizzle of oil to same pan over medium-high heat. Add @diced chicken thighs{10%oz} and a big pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1%unit} and @water{1/4%cup} until combined. Bring to a simmer and cook until mixture is saucy and chicken is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Turn off heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp}, lime zest, and half the cilantro. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice between bowls and top with veggies, saucy chicken, salsa, crema, remaining cilantro, and any remaining sauce from pan. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.